# Third-party licenses

Veld's binaries (`veld`, `veld-helper`, `veld-daemon`, `veld-gateway`) statically
link the Rust crates listed below, and this file reproduces each crate's license
text to carry those notices with the distributed binaries. It is generated by
[`cargo-about`](https://github.com/EmbarkStudios/cargo-about) — do not edit by
hand; run `just licenses` to regenerate.

This project's peer-to-peer transport is built on
[iroh](https://github.com/n0-computer/iroh) (dual-licensed MIT / Apache-2.0).
Crates offered under `MIT OR Apache-2.0` are listed below under Apache-2.0, the
arm Veld elects; complying with one arm of an `OR` license satisfies it.

**Source and further notices.** The complete corresponding source of every crate
here — including any `NOTICE` file it ships (Apache-2.0 §4(d)) and the source of
any [MPL-2.0](https://www.mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/)-covered files (MPL-2.0 §3.2) — is
published on [crates.io](https://crates.io) at the crate's name and version, and
at the repository linked beside each crate below. Veld redistributes these crates
unmodified.

